docs.abstract: When Marriott acquired Starwood Hotels, Starwood Preferred Guest members feared the worst. Our resident Starwood fan thinks the new program is worth trying.
docs.snippet: When Marriott acquired Starwood Hotels, Starwood Preferred Guest members feared the worst. Our resident Starwood fan thinks the new program is worth trying.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the nearly two and a half years since Marriott announced its intention to acquire Starwood Hotels and Resorts, the parent of Westin, Sheraton and W, skeptical customers of both companies have waited impatiently for answers to the following question: Just how many rewards and perks would Marriott take away from the 110 million members when it combined the loyalty programs?

headline.main: Marriott’s New Loyalty Program: Not as Bad as Starwood Fans Feared
headline.print_headline: Revisions To Marriott Points Plan Seem Fair

docs.abstract: After Equifax’s security breach, consumers looked for ways to make the company pay. One option: Persuade employers not to give the company any data.
docs.snippet: After Equifax’s security breach, consumers looked for ways to make the company pay. One option: Persuade employers not to give the company any data.
docs.lead_paragraph: After the Equifax data breach in early September, readers asked one question repeatedly that had no good answer: Was there any way to punish the company?

headline.main: You Can’t Fire Equifax, but Your Employer Can. Mine Just Did.
headline.print_headline: Quit Equifax? Unlike You, Employers Can

docs.abstract: A bipartisan effort to tax Washington workers and offer a year of nursing home or other coverage is mired in questions over caregiver qualifications.
docs.snippet: A bipartisan effort to tax Washington workers and offer a year of nursing home or other coverage is mired in questions over caregiver qualifications.
docs.lead_paragraph: OLYMPIA, Wash. — For a few weeks this year, the rarest of things seemed like it was about to occur. A state, in this case Washington, was working to pass a bill that would institute a new payroll tax to help cover the cost of a much-needed service: long-term care in a nursing home, in a personal residence or elsewhere in the local community.

headline.main: One State’s Quest to Introduce Long-Term Care Benefits
headline.print_headline: One State’s Quest to Offer  Long-Term Care Benefits

docs.abstract: After the ‘most tweeted’ State of the Union speech ever, Megyn Kelly and Chris Christie try out new roles, and Van Jones comes out swinging.
docs.snippet: After the ‘most tweeted’ State of the Union speech ever, Megyn Kelly and Chris Christie try out new roles, and Van Jones comes out swinging.
docs.lead_paragraph: The truth-squad website PolitiFact crashed just 30 minutes in. A C-Span shot of Representative Nancy Pelosi, scowling and clad entirely in black, quickly became a meme. And the former Fox News anchor Megyn Kelly, making her debut as a prime time NBC political analyst, declared that President Trump “did a fine job — but I think he’s going to tweet something and we’ll forget all about it.”

docs.abstract: Mr. Scaramucci, the voluble former White House communications director, is a co-executive producer of HBO’s “Paterno.” It started with an acquaintance made on an Oliver Stone film.
docs.snippet: Mr. Scaramucci, the voluble former White House communications director, is a co-executive producer of HBO’s “Paterno.” It started with an acquaintance made on an Oliver Stone film.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eagle-eyed viewers of the HBO film “Paterno” — a biopic of the disgraced Penn State football coach, starring a slurring, pancake-faced Al Pacino — may spot a surprising name in the credits: Anthony Scaramucci, the world’s most famous former White House communications director.

headline.main: Pacino as Paterno, and Who Is That Producer? Anthony Scaramucci
headline.print_headline: A Producer on His Role:  He Supplied ‘the Dough’
